description: For sale: $339,900. This is one you have to see! Stepping inside this home, it grows and expands before your eyes!  This Esko ranch style home offers tons of space for you in a convenient location! The 3+ bedroom, 2+ bath home sits on 5 acres with all the updates and amenities you're looking for!  The kitchen includes a useful island/breakfast bar, updated appliances, and a nice birch kitchen to give you that "home-y" feel! The dining room is large and would be perfect for that big dining room table! A wood stove was added to the stone fireplace in this room to bring added heat and comfort to the home! The living room is expansive with vaulted ceilings and a wall of windows to let the sun in! From here, you can go out to the 700 sq ft deck to enjoy time outdoors! A Master bedroom on this floor includes vaulted ceilings, oversized closet, and a full en-suite bath complete with jacuzzi tub!  Two more bedrooms and a full bath complete the rest of the main floor! Follow the wide staircase down to the lower level and you'll find a massive family/rec room space complete with home theater! If that wasn't enough, a Finlandia sauna is located just right off this room and is huge! The Sellers finished an additional family room area with two rooms off of it currently used as bedrooms! One thing that doesn't lack in this lower level is storage, there's tons of it! Lower level also includes a laundry room and in-floor heat (and throughout the home)! Outside you'll find a wonderful 3 car garage and an additional 1 car garage, perfect for boat or other storage. A brand new well drilled last year, vinyl siding, city sewer, and so much more make this home maintenance free and move-in ready!

description: For sale: $699,900. Welcome to 75 Parkview Lane.  This home will have the all of your needs checked off.  Home features 10 acres, 3 bedrooms, 3 baths, open floor plans on all levels for entertaining guests, garages (2 are heated) to hold all of your vehicles/toys, with one of the garages set up for a mother-in-law or guest suite.  As soon as you walk into this home you will notice the Great Room that overlooks the park-like backyard and the wood burning fireplace that has a rock surround with a wood mantle. The main level features a kitchen that is complete with Heartland high-end appliances, a dining room with views for miles and access to the spacious deck. To finish off the main level is the Master Bedroom with a walk-in closet. The Lower Level features a family room with another wood-burning fireplace and opens up to the billiards room with a beautiful tin ceiling. Step out the lower level to a covered patio, firepit, manicured backyard and even enjoy the 10x20 sauna.  The top level of this home will have 2 spacious bedrooms, a bathroom and an area in the hallway to set-up for studying or just relaxing.  This home is within 20 minutes of Duluth, trails to access Jay Cooke State Park just outside of the property lines and room to house horses.  This home truly has it all.

Quality home construction built by Everest Construction Group and 3W Development. Contact us directly for a showing. Follow us at #everestgroupMN on Instagram!

description:
Recently sold: $385,000. Great home in the desirable Esko School District!  Located on three acres on paved road and within two miles of the school.  Only 15 minutes to Duluth and quick access to all Northern Minnesota has to offer.    This home features three generous bedrooms and two bathrooms on a slab foundation.   

The welcoming entry to the home features a large covered Brazilian hardwood deck, trimmed with Cedar and sports a Cedar ceiling.   Upon entry you will be greeted by slate flooring with a spacious front entry closet.  The Oak hardwood flooring expands across the open floor plan guiding your view through spacious living area and up into loft and the Cedar finished vaulted ceiling.   As you step onto the slate and hardwood flooring you will appreciate the warmth of the in-floor radiant heat.   You will also appreciate the warm presence and beauty of the freestanding Quadra Fire gas stove resting on reclaimed barn wood timbers.   The natural trim work is exceptional featuring two piece solid Birch.  The multitude of Marvin Integrity windows allows for natural lighting and expands your view throughout the property.   

The kitchen is spacious with expansive counter tops and allows for six full height stools to entertain your guests.   The cabinets are custom built of Hickory.   The dining area joins the living space and vaulted sun room with a large glass patio door that overlooks the large backyard.   The arched entry to the vaulted sun room adds to the quality craftsmanship of the home.  Upon entering you will enjoy slate floors and 180 degree views of your property.    

Down the hallway you have a main floor bathroom with slate floors and beyond that are the two main floor bedrooms.  Both have solid wood core doors and feature top of the line Emtek hardware as you will find throughout the house.   The bedrooms are spacious and are perfect for the growing family.  Beyond the solid wood French doors, the closets feature Maple built-ins.  

On the main floor you will also find the laundry room, large utility room, and rear entry.  Again the warmth and feel of the slate floors bring a luxurious feel, and the custom built Hickory cabinets add to the presence of a solid home.   The utility features all the comforts one would require in Northern Minnesota.   You will have a brand new on demand gas boiler supporting both radiant heat and domestic hot water.  The electric furnace is there for a boost of back up heat if needed and also doubles as your central air conditioner in the summer.   The air exchanger keeps the humidity just right and the air fresh while saving energy costs.   Great tasting water from your well is also filtered and softened keeping your pipes and fixtures operating like new.   This is where the central vacuum supports the multiple connection points throughout the house including a kick plate in the kitchen.   

Heading up the solid wood stairs to the loft you will enjoy the strength and durability of the solid Alder rail system.  The loft features a large pentagonal picture window overlooking the Western horizon.  Off the spacious loft area is the Master Bedroom which houses a spacious walk in closet and Master Bath.   The walk in closet includes Maple built-ins.  The Master Bath includes a large shower, double sinks, Maple cabinets, and a jetted tub.   

Outside the landscape is three acres offering privacy but also a great neighborly feel.  The large paved driveway leads you to a generous 36'x32' three car garage with storage above.  The property features a large yard surrounding the house and garage with a pond in the back.  Plenty of shade is provided from the mature trees.  The exterior of the house is clad in newly installed LP Smartside siding.   

This home is truly exceptional and in a great Northern Minnesota town.   Call now to make an appointment for your showing.

description: Recently sold: $305,000. Beautiful landscaped and settled in to the White Pines and Maple trees is where you will find this NICE 3 bedroom Rambler.  This home is bright and open offering both a formal living room area and a family room with gas fireplace. The kitchen is big and centrally located for entertaining. Main floor laundry, master suite and air conditioning are just a few of the things you will love about this home. The Lower Level basement has 2 egress windows just waiting for you to finish off how ever you would like. There is storage shelving and a utilities area.  All of this on 5 private acres near Jay Cooke State Park. Very close to Duluth, AND located in the ESKO school district!

Recently sold: $474,900. Private, 5 acres of wooded land on the edge of Jay Cooke State Park.  The property is just around the corner from the Munger bike trail and hiking trails within the park.  Newer custom built house finished in 2013 offers 3,109 sq feet of living space, 4+ bedroom and 3 bathrooms. The  main floor oversized master bedroom has a walk in closet and on suite bathroom, jacuzzi tub, walk in shower, double vanities.  Entryway has custom mudroom built in lockers, main floor laundry, and an office.  Upstairs are 3+ bedrooms and second living room, plus over sized finished bonus room.  The bonus room can serve as a 5th bedroom with walk in closet.  This home also has an attached, finished and heated 30x36 garage and detached 24x30 garage.  Dual fuel heating, heated slab/forced air furnace,  heat pump/A/C and gas fire place.  Granite and upgrades throughout the home.  Step outside from the dining room or master bedroom to a patio with pergola. On this land are trails, a pond and lots of wild life.  You don?t want to miss this one!  Call 218-590-4208 for more information or to schedule a showing!

description: Recently sold: $319,900. Esko is home to this spacious 4+ BR, 4 BA home on a beautifully maintained corner lot. The open main floor living area includes an updated eat-in kitchen with stainless steel appliances. Enjoy the fantastic views if the mature trees through the bay window in the living room. Also, on the main floor is a bedroom, remodeled full bath and an office or formal dining room. The second floor offers three bedrooms and two full baths including a master bedroom suite. description: Recently sold: $330,000. JUST BUILT in 2016. The builder built for personal residence it is not a spec house. Home has many great features you are expecting but then some you're not. The sealed concrete counters are beautiful, copper farm sink, stainless appliances, plank tile floors, Full master suite w large walk in closet & private bath. Open floor plan, dining w access to grilling patio out back. Vaulted ceiling, att 24x24 garage could be converted to a family room. There is a LARGE parking pad already prepped for a future 40x40 garage if wanted or RV parking. 24x26 det gar is older then house needs a little work but its just bonus garage space.
